'''Ōarahiko Shrine / Tomoyui Shrine''' (おおあらひこじんじゃ・ともゆいじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=Shinto shrine|Q845945|WD=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} complex in Ura, Makino-chō, {{ill|lt=Takashima, Shiga|Q845794|WD=Q845794|1=Takashima, Shiga}}, {{ill|lt=Shiga Prefecture|Q131358|WD=Q131358|1=Shiga Prefecture}}. Two shrines are jointly enshrined in one listing, and both are treated as candidate shrines for {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Shikinaisha|1=Shikinaisha|WD=Q134917286}}. Former shrine rank: {{ill|lt=Gōsha|Q134917316|WD=Q134917316|1=Gō-sha}}.

=== Enshrined deities ===
;Ōarahiko Shrine
:*{{ill|lt=Toyoki-iribiko-no-Mikoto|Q11633375|WD=Q11633375|1=Prince Toyokiirihiko}}
:*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Ōaratawake-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}
:*{{ill|Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|lt=Ōnamuchi-no-Mikoto|WD=Q276944|1=Ōkuninushi}}
:*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Suserihime-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}
:*Associated deities: {{ill|Susanoo-no-Mikoto|lt=Susanoo-no-Mikoto|WD=Q272993|1=Susanoo-no-Mikoto}} / {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Sugawara no Michizane|1=UNKNOWN}}
;Tomoyui Shrine
:*{{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Homudawake-no-Mikoto|1=UNKNOWN}}

=== Shrine crest ===
Kuwagata

=== History ===
According to shrine tradition, it was founded in the reign of {{ill|lt=Emperor Chūai|Q179971|WD=Q179971|1=Emperor Chūai}}, and later revered as the {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=sōsha|1=UNKNOWN}} of Tomoyui-go (Tomoyui-shō). Both Tomoyui Shrine and Ōarahiko Shrine are identified as Shikinaisha, and both have other candidate shrines.

In {{ill|lt=1876|Q7766|WD=Q7766|1=1876}} (Meiji 9), it was ranked as gōsha.

